"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228267","HM Treasury","false","2015-03-23","<p>The Treasury Ministers discuss a variety of issues with Ministers from other government departments throughout the year, including the run up to Budget.</p><p> </p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-03-23T15:27:52.14Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228267/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228267/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228267/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-03-18","Alcoholic Drinks: Excise Duties","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what discussions Ministers in his Department had with the Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State for Public Health on alcohol duty prior to the publication of the Budget 2015; what issues were raised during those discussions; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","228208"
