ment Bank for UK community scale renewable energy projects.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","228195 ; 228197","2015-03-23T16:23:08.9Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228268/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228268/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228268/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-03-18","Energy: Tax Allowances","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will take steps to clarify when measures in the Autumn Statement 2014 which relate to the tax treatment of UK community energy co-operatives will take effect.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","228198"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228269","HM Treasury","false","2015-03-25","<p>By the tax year beginning April 2017 this Government's increases in the personal allowance (for those born after 5 April 1948) are forecast to have reduced the income tax liability of 27.2 million individuals in the UK. It is forecast that 2.9 million of them live in the North West and Merseyside region, which includes the Parliamentary Constituency of Pendle.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>These forecasts are based on the 2012-13 Survey of Personal Incomes, projected to 2017-18 using economic assumptions consistent with the Office for Budget Responsibility’s March 2015 economic and fiscal outlook.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>HM Treasury does not publish this information at constituency level.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-03-25T10:55:30.017Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228269/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228269/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228269/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-03-18","Income Tax: Pendle","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many people in Pendle constituency had their income tax reduced as a result of personal allowance increases since May 2010.","false","Biography information for Andrew Stephenson","Pendle","Andrew Stephenson","228200"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228270","HM Treasury","false","2015-03-26","<p>The Green Investment Bank (GIB) has a budget of £3.8bn and there is no immediate need for the bank to borrow.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>As set out in ‘investing in Britain’s future’, the GIB has the power to borrow from the NLF if desired.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-03-26T13:35:15.863Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228270/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228270/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228270/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-03-18","Green Investment Bank","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, by what date does he plan to grant the Green Investment Bank powers to borrow from the private capital markets.","false","Biography information for Joan Walley","Stoke-on-Trent North","Joan Walley","228182"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228271","HM Treasury","false","2015-03-23","<p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) has been discussing a vision of its future to 2020 and beyond with its workforce, through a consultation process called Building our Future. Through this, HMRC has outlined how it proposes to transform services to its customers and set out what this means for the future size, shape and location of the Department.<br><br>All HMRC staff members in every office have been invited to participate in Building our Future events, and around 80 per cent of staff have attended around 1,300 events across the UK in the two phases held so far.<br><br>HMRC also shared the main elements of this vision with MPs and Assembly Members in October 14. HMRC will continue to keep MPs and Assembly Members informed of the outcomes of these conversations.<br><br>HMRC has set out its early thinking about the principles that will determine its future location strategy, which involves bringing teams closer together in a smaller number of large, modern, adaptable Regional Centres. These centres will be supported by a UK-wide network of smaller specialist and touchdown sites. <br><br>HMRC has told staff that it believes that Cardiff is the most suitable location for a future Regional Centre in Wales, since it is already the biggest HMRC location in the country. However, no firm decisions have yet been made on the precise location or timing of a new HMRC Regional Centre in Cardiff or the nature and timing of impacts on other HMRC locations in Wales. <br><br>HMRC will be developing its plans over coming months and will share details of them as they emerge. HMRC will naturally undertake all necessary consultations and impact assessments.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","228093 ; 228099 ; 228103 ; 228104","2015-03-23T16:12:39.82Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228271/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228271/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228271/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-03-18","Revenue and Customs: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with whom he consulted prior to making proposals on the future of HM Revenue and Customs offices in Wales as part of the Building our Future programme.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian Lucas","228187"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228272","HM Treasury","false","2015-03-26","<p>The Financial Services and Markets Act 2000 requires the Prudential Regulation Authority and Financial Conduct Authority to include consideration of the principles of good regulation in their annual report.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>These statutory principles of good regulation include “the desirability of sustainable growth in the economy of the United Kingdom in the medium or long term”.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-03-26T13:24:31.93Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228272/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228272/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228272/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-03-18","Financial Markets","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the Answer of 9 March 2015 to Question 225717, if he will request that the Prudential Regulation Authority and the Financial Conduct Authority report on their performance in relation to sustainable growth in their annual reports.","false","Biography information for Joan Walley","Stoke-on-Trent North","Joan Walley","228181"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228273","HM Treasury","false","2015-03-23","<p>A Tax Information and Impact Note was published on 10 December 2013 which included an assessment of the expected impact on small and micro businesses. It is available at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/264647/Overview_of_legislation_in_draft.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/264647/Overview_of_legislation_in_draft.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>I refer the Hon. Lady to the answer that I gave on 10 December 2014.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-03-23T16:07:46.71Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228273/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228273/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228273/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-03-18","ICT: VAT","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the effect on UK micro businesses of EU digital VAT legislation since its implementation on 1 January 2015; what discussions he has had with such businesses on the effect of that legislation; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","228209"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228274","HM Treasury","false","2015-03-23","<p>VAT is not due on fines and similar penalties levied in connection with parking.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","228269","2015-03-23T16:08:54.137Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228274/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228274/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228274/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-03-18","Parking: Fines","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether parking notices (a) constitute taxable supply and (b) are subject to VAT.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","228248"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228275","HM Treasury","false","2015-03-24","<p>HM Revenue &amp; Customs (HMRC) has appointed a Modern Slavery Strategic Lead and is fully involved in delivering the cross-Government strategy to tackle Modern Slavery. As part of this, HMRC has developed an internal Action Plan which includes training for visiting officers to improve the coordination of HMRC operations where modern slavery is suspected to be taking place. HMRC will work in collaboration with other government agencies where appropriate. There are no plans to publish the Action Plan.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-03-24T17:57:54.93Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228275/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228275/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228275/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-03-18","Slavery","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the Answer of 2 February 2015 to Question 221881, whether he expects to publish the Action Plan on Modern Slavery before the Dissolution of Parliament.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","228290"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228276","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-03-23","<p /> <p>My Department has not received any recent representations from the pensions industry on investments in companies linked with the manufacture of cluster munitions. Whilst we have no immediate plans to review this specific area, we are undertaking a consultation on whether the current requirements on trustees regarding “social, environmental or ethical considerations” in the Occupational Pension Schemes (Investment) Regulations 2015 should be amended to help them distinguish between financial and non-financial factors.</p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb","228250 ; 228251 ; 228253","2015-03-23T15:04:54.37Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228276/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228276/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228276/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-03-18","Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what plans his Department has to review the ability of pensions schemes to indirectly invest in companies linked with the manufacture of cluster munitions.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","228249"
